-- J.C. Penney February same-store sales fall 6.7 pct
-- 
-- Thu Mar 6, 2008 9:10am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/06/us-usa-retailsales-jcpenney-idUSWNAS383120080306

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - J.C. Penney Co Inc ( JCP.N ) said on Thursday its February sales at department stores open at least a year fell 6.7 percent, and it forecast another decline in March. 

 Analysts, on average, were expecting February same-store sales to fall 1.9 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. J.C. Penney shares dropped almost 5 percent in premarket trading to $46.00. The Plano, Texas-based company said total sales declined 4.4 percent to $1.26 billion in the four weeks ended March 1. The company had forecast total sales would be about flat and same-department store sales would decrease by a low-single-digit percentage. Home products continued to show the worst sales, J.C. Penney said in a statement. The company forecast a low-single-digit decline in same-store sales for the five-week March reporting period, which ends April 5. Total sales for March are expected to be about flat, the company said. (Reporting by  Brad Dorfman , editing by Gerald E. McCormick and John Wallace)